Use register_sysctl_sz directly with an explicit cast for the table pointer.

The original `register_sysctl(path, raid_table)` macro expands to
`register_sysctl_sz(path, raid_table, ARRAY_SIZE(raid_table))`. On pre-6.6
kernels register_sysctl_sz takes `struct ctl_table *` (non-const), and
raid_table is `static const struct ctl_table[]`, so the implicit conversion
drops const and triggers -Werror=discarded-qualifiers.

A direct cast inside the macro doesn't help because ARRAY_SIZE then sees a
pointer instead of an array. So we expand the macro by hand: cast only the
table argument, while keeping `raid_table` (still in scope as an array) for
ARRAY_SIZE. The cast is a benign const-drop on newer kernels where the
parameter is already const.

--- a/md.c
+++ b/md.c
@@ -10745,7 +10745,9 @@
 	mdp_major = ret;
 
 	register_reboot_notifier(&md_notifier);
-	raid_table_header = register_sysctl("dev/raid", raid_table);
+	raid_table_header = register_sysctl_sz("dev/raid",
+					       (struct ctl_table *)raid_table,
+					       ARRAY_SIZE(raid_table));
 
 	md_geninit();
 	return 0;
